 One of the featres of HPS experiment is that, in nominal production running condition
 the distance between the beam and the physical edge of the 1st layer of Silicon Vertex Tracker (SVT) is
 $0.5\;mm$, and the silicon sensor is far from the beam by $1.5\;mm$. Beam vertical movement more than $1.5\;mm$ 
 migh damage the silicon sensor.
 
 The goal of this works is to study whether beam moves vertically during the beam trips or not.
 
 
